cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it explores the use of a morphological hit-or-miss transform in deep neural networks for image analysis. It also involves benchmarking on image datasets. 

The paper also involves optimization and learning, which suggests it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

The use of alternative foundations for neural networks, such as morphology, could also place this paper in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper introduces an extension of convolution, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as convolution is commonly used in image and video processing.
